properties.name: CurrentStateId
properties.description: This attribute give the current state of the object in its object live.

properties.name: GlobalExpense
properties.description: aggregation of costs of Applications + Deployment of Application for the current year

properties.name: CurrentNumberofUsers
properties.description: Sum of the numbers of users specified on all deployment context that are in production today.

properties.name: CostperUser
properties.description: Calculate the cost per user (aggregation of costs of Applications + Deployment of Application divided by all users specified on deployment context).

properties.name: RankAPM
properties.description: The Rank summarizes the evaluation criteria of the applicaction: the technical efficiency, the functional support and business value. If the sum of the evaluation criteria gives: 3 or 4 the Rank is 1 star5 or 6 the Rank is 2 stars 7 or 8 the Rank is 3 stars 9 or 10 the Rank is 4 stars 11 or 12 the Rank is 5 stars If the sum is less than 3 the application is ranked 0 stars.

properties.name: TechnologyCompliance
properties.description: Technological compliance is calculated as follows:If all technologies used by the application have as enterprise Standard the value  Recommended , technology Compliance takes the value  Recommended .If one of the technologies used by the application has as enterprise Standard the value  Prohibited , technology Compliance takes the value  Prohibited .If at least one of the technologies used by the application has as enterprise Standard the value  Accepted  ,technology Compliance takes the value  Accepted . If the application does not use any technology, or if all technologies used by the application have as enterprise Standard the value  Unknown , technology Compliance takes the value  Unknown .

properties.name: FunctionalSupportAPM

properties.name: TechnicalEfficiencyAPM

properties.name: SoftwareResiliencyScoreCASTHighligh
properties.description: Express in %.Software Resiliency indicates programming best practices that make software bullet-proof, more robust and secure. This index is derived through technology-specific code analysis that searches for the presence of code patterns and bad programming practices that may comprise the reliability of the software at short term. Higher is the Software Resiliency, lower is the likelihood of defects occurring in production.Metric powered by CAST Highlight

properties.name: SoftwareResiliencyThresholdsCASTHighligh
properties.description: Thresholds used for Software Resiliency:High (green): value >= 71.0 Medium (orange): value >= 57.0 Low (red): value < 57.0Metric powered by CAST Highlight

properties.name: SoftwareAgilityScore
properties.description: Express in %.Software Agility indicates the easiness of a development team to understand and maintain an application. This index is derived through technology-specific code analysis that searches for the presence of embedded documentation and code readability good practices.Metric powered by CAST Highlight

properties.name: SoftwareAgilityThresholdsCASTHighligh
properties.description: Thresholds used for Software Agility categories:High (green): value >= 78.0Medium (orange): value >= 51.0Low (red): value < 51.0Metric powered by CAST Highlight

properties.name: SoftwareEleganceScoreCASTHighligh
properties.description: Express in %.Software Elegance measures the ability to deliver software value with less code complexity. A low Software Elegance score indicates decreased quality in the code resulting in higher defects that become costly to fix at mid-term.Metric powered by CAST Highlight

properties.name: SoftwareEleganceThresholdsCASTHighligh
properties.description: Thresholds used for Software Elegance categories:High (green): value >= 88.0Medium (orange): value >= 66.0Low (red): value < 66.0Metric powered by CAST Highlight

properties.name: CloudReadyScoreCASTHighlight
properties.description: Express in %. Formula use the survey point reference and applay loss and gain points from the source code scan.

properties.name: CloudReadyScanCASTHighlight

properties.name: WorkRecoveryTimeWRT
properties.description: The Work Recovery Time (WRT) determines the maximum tolerable amount of time that is needed to verify the system and or data integrity. This could be, for example, checking the databases and logs, making sure the applications or services are running and are available.Four levels of WRT need to be specified:- Critical (maximum tolerable amount of time that is needed to verify the system and or data integrity is seconds)- Serious (maximum tolerable amount of time that is needed to verify the system and or data integrity is minutes)- Significant (maximum tolerable amount of time that is needed to verify the system and or data integrity is hours)- Minor (maximum tolerable amount of time that is needed to verify the system and or data integrity is days)

properties.name: MaximumTolerableDowntimeMTD
properties.description: Maximum Tolerable Downtime (MTD) determines the maximum time a business can tolerate the absence or unavailability of a particular application.Downtime consists of two elements, the Recovery Time Objective and the Work Recovery Time: MTD = RTO + WRTMTD level will be calculated automatically according to RTO and WRT levels, it cannot be modified manually.-	Critical (maximum tolerable downtime is seconds)-	Serious (maximum tolerable downtime is minutes)-	Significant (maximum tolerable downtime is hours)-	Minor (maximum tolerable downtime is days)

properties.name: SLALevel
properties.description: Service-level Agreement (SLA) is a contract between a service provider and its internal or external customers that documents what services the provider will furnish, to calculate the SLA, HOPEX users (Portfolio Manager, Application Owner) will need to fill information on:- Recovery point objective (RPO)- Recovery time objective (RTO)- Work Recovery Time (WRT)- Maximum Tolerable Downtime (MTD)Then a SLA value will be proposed by HOPEX, if the result is not in line with user expectation, he will be able to change the SLA value manually.

properties.name: Loop
properties.description: A loop is a process step that is repeated as long as a condition is true: - Do While: the condition is evaluated before the first execution. - Do Until: the condition is evaluated after the first execution. In this case, the process step is executed at least once.

properties.name: AdHoc
properties.description: Steps of an ad hoc process are not controlled or sequenced in a particular order. Theirperformance is determined by the performers of the process.

properties.name: Multiple
properties.description: The process step is repeated a number of times that is evaluated only once before it is performed. It can be repeated in parallel or sequentially.

properties.name: Compensation

properties.name: Numberofincidents

properties.name: LoopCondition
